title: For Trade:  TRADE- Rare Antique Georgian Era 1700's 0.52 Carat VS2 G Old Mine Cushion Cut Diamond Ring
postcontent: I have a rare 1700's Georgian Era 0.52 carat VS2 G Antique Mine Cushion Cut Diamond Ring set in 14k Yellow Gold. They Are extremely hard to find, more valuable than modern cut diamonds and truly a unique diamond. The gold setting is detailed with a scolled top and a raised box prong head in white gold. It's a statement piece for that special someone, or as an investment. Over the last decade the demand for these has sky rocketed, only problem, not many have survived the last 40-50 years of diamond cutters cutting them into brilliant cuts. So with that being said, over the last 10ish years, demand has gone up, value has jumped greatly as well because of the demand it's more than what's available. Also Over the past few years, an increase of roughly 15-20% in value has been very steady on these.Appraised value is $3,520, but I'm not looking to sell it but trade it.Estate jewelers pay between 35-45% of appraised value to turn around to retail it.
